<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br> 
Acts of Parliament do not need to be added to the reference list unless there are details in the 
reference which are important to the understanding of your essay. Acts of Parliament should be 
listed separately under the heading &#8216;Legislation&#8217;.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">
	<em>Title of Act Year Act was made law</em> (Jurisdiction) Section and Subsections of Act, 
	viewed date, &lt;URL&gt;.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Examples</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Act Year Act was made law">Corporations Act 2001</span></em>
	(<span class="hover" title="Jurisdiction">Commonwealth of Australia</span>)
	<span class="hover" title="Section and Subsections of Act">s. 3</span>,
	viewed <span class="hover" title="viewed date">19 May 2009</span>,
