<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
Titles of Acts and other legislation should be cited exactly as they appear, and punctuation 
should not be altered to suit the reference style. After the first citation, the date can be 
omitted from the citation.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	<em>Section 3 of the Corporations Act 2001</em> (Cwlth) states that&hellip;
	<br>
	or
	<br>
	Corporations must&hellip; (<em>Corporations Act 2001</em> (Cwlth), s.3)
</blockquote>
